or security screening.<br />\n<br />\nThe radiation dose typically received by objects scanned by a cabinet x-ray system is 1 millirad or less. The average dose rate from background radiation is 360 millirad per year. The minimum dose used in food irradiation for food preservation or destruction of parasites or pathogens is 30,000 rad.<br />\n<br />\nsource: <a href=\"https://www.fda.gov/Radiation-EmittingProducts/RadiationEmittingProductsandProcedures/SecuritySystems/ucm116421.htm\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2FRadiation-EmittingProducts%2FRadiationEmittingProductsandProcedures%2FSecuritySystems%2Fucm116421.htm&d=juZNQ8TWd%2FZKTWwpyWEy8mi1w7%2FDyS2Kz%2BsYtkalU0Y%3D&h=b6cae7f3\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.fda.gov/Radiation-EmittingProducts/RadiationEmittingProductsandProcedures/SecuritySystems/ucm116421.htm</a><br />\n<br />\n1millirad = 0.01 milligray (mGy)<br />\n1張CXR先得0.1mGy<br />\n請問點樣大過CT???<br />\n<br />\n你睇佢幅相。根本完全打唔穿個人體。得條femur同tibia fibula 叫勉強睇到下.....<br />\n<br />\n同埋, 你CT係不斷咁支tube轉360度helical scan 咁去掃個region of interest再砌返d slice出來。你依家一張過。我最多咪當你好似fluoroscopy咁。有乜可能大電過CT??"}]}